A commenter observed that  388.1 should be revised, and the regulations changed throughout, to emphasize human
resource development in place of training. Peer reviewers should be oriented to human resource development prior
to their service as reviewers. The Secretary agrees that the term human resource development is descriptive of many
appropriate activities under this program. However, the Rehabilitation Act of 1973, as amended, uses the term ``in-service
